# secrets.env.example — template for your secrets.env (copy it, then fill in)
#
# secrets.env holds EVERY secret value in one place: chmod 600, never mounted
# into containers. up.sh composes per-container credentials from it according
# to what each containers/<name>.yml grants. It lives at
# $DEV_AGENT_HOME/secrets.env — by default the gitignored ./.dev-agent/secrets.env
# inside this repo, or your own path if you set DEV_AGENT_HOME in ./.env.
#
#   cp secrets.env.example .dev-agent/secrets.env && chmod 600 .dev-agent/secrets.env
#   then fill in the values below (leave unused lines out)

# ── Service tokens ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Host-service plugins self-generate their token here on the first
# `./service.sh <name>` run — no need to create them by hand. Each plugin's token
# variable is documented in its plugins/<name>/README.md.

# ── GitHub machine user ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Fine-grained PAT from the machine account (NOT your personal account):
# Contents RW, Pull requests RW, Issues RW, Actions R, Checks R. No Workflows.
# Agents act as this identity; your own gh login stays in shared/gh.
GH_TOKEN=github_pat_xxxxxxxxxxxx

# ── Obsidian Annotated identities ────────────────────────────────────────────
# One key per container+agent pair, minted in Settings → Annotated.
# Convention: OBSIDIAN_KEY_<container>_<agent>, dashes become underscores.
# Additive tier for normal agents; destructive only for vault maintenance;
# poll-tier keys (watchers) use the OBSIDIAN_WATCH_KEY_ prefix.
#
# These examples match containers/TEMPLATE.yml's example identities:
OBSIDIAN_KEY_personal_site_claude=ann_additive_xxxxxxxx
OBSIDIAN_KEY_default_gemini=ann_additive_xxxxxxxx
OBSIDIAN_WATCH_KEY_personal_site_claude=ann_poll_xxxxxxxx

# ── SSH (remote hosts only) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Your PUBLIC key, injected at runtime into containers whose manifest has an
# ssh: section (homelab/VPS editor access). Not needed on the Mac.
#SSH_AUTHORIZED_KEY="ssh-ed25519 AAAA... your@machine"

# ── Remote-access notifications (remote.notify: ntfy) ────────────────────────
# Your ntfy server base URL (self-hosted or ntfy.sh) and topic. Containers
# whose manifest sets remote.notify: ntfy get these in their env and the
# host auto-added to their egress allowlist; an agent going idle at a
# prompt pushes to the topic.
#NTFY_URL=https://ntfy.example.com
#NTFY_TOPIC=dev-agents
